			"version": 331,
			"versionNonce": 158028047,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1774189231091,
			"link": null,
			"locked": true,
			"text": "Assumption that conflicts between txns is rare. So no locking should\noccur.\nThe txns are completely normal, acting as if no other txn exists.\nBut at commit time a validation is run. It is jsut like git merge\nconflict resolution. No conflict? No problem, a Conflict? abort one of\nthe commits.",
			"rawText": "Assumption that conflicts between txns is rare. So no locking should occur.\nThe txns are completely normal, acting as if no other txn exists. But at commit time a validation is run. It is jsut like git merge conflict resolution. No conflict? No problem, a Conflict? abort one of the commits.",
			"fontSize": 20,
			"fontFamily": 5,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "Assumption that conflicts between txns is rare. So no locking should occur.\nThe txns are completely normal, acting as if no other txn exists. But at commit time a validation is run. It is jsut like git merge conflict resolution. No conflict? No problem, a Conflict? abort one of the commits.",
			"autoResize": false,
			"lineHeight": 1.25
		},
