		{
			"id": "OpsFiv49",
			"type": "text",
			"x": 244.09800865581224,
			"y": 1198.7864135558061,
			"width": 993.2594604492188,
			"height": 200,
			"angle": 0,
			"strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
			"backgroundColor": "transparent",
			"fillStyle": "solid",
			"strokeWidth": 1,
			"strokeStyle": "solid",
			"roughness": 0,
			"opacity": 100,
			"groupIds": [
				"Z5_nwVSeBAAo7KFivKjTT"
			],
			"frameId": null,
			"index": "b7Cr",
			"roundness": null,
			"seed": 1731838475,
			"version": 805,
			"versionNonce": 1474220431,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [
				{
					"id": "sB8XptJn-ISOPxlq57h78",
					"type": "arrow"
				}
			],
			"updated": 1774189231091,
			"link": null,
			"locked": true,
			"text": "OCC\nEvery txn keeps its own set of reads and writes it has done.\n\nPoint is we want to know that when these sort of situations occur:\n    T1 and T2 started at the same time. T1 wrote to X, and T2 is read X before this update by T1.\nTransactions execute without locks.\nImportant to remember OCC doesn't maintain a version record like MVCC.\nThis checking is ONLY done at the commit time.",
			"rawText": "OCC\nEvery txn keeps its own set of reads and writes it has done.\n\nPoint is we want to know that when these sort of situations occur:\n    T1 and T2 started at the same time. T1 wrote to X, and T2 is read X before this update by T1.\nTransactions execute without locks.\nImportant to remember OCC doesn't maintain a version record like MVCC.\nThis checking is ONLY done at the commit time.",
			"fontSize": 20,
			"fontFamily": 5,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "OCC\nEvery txn keeps its own set of reads and writes it has done.\n\nPoint is we want to know that when these sort of situations occur:\n    T1 and T2 started at the same time. T1 wrote to X, and T2 is read X before this update by T1.\nTransactions execute without locks.\nImportant to remember OCC doesn't maintain a version record like MVCC.\nThis checking is ONLY done at the commit time.",
